headline: United Rentals’s (NYSE:URI) Q3 Sales Top Estimates
summary: Equipment rental company United Rentals (NYSE:URI) reported Q3 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 5.9% year on year to $4.23 billion. The company expects the full year’s revenue to be around $16.1 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $11.70 per share was 4.9% below analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: United Rentals Declares Quarterly Cash Dividend
summary: STAMFORD, Conn., October 22, 2025--United Rentals, Inc. (NYSE: URI) announced today that its Board of Directors declared a quarterly cash dividend of $1.79 per share of URI common stock. The dividend will be payable on November 26, 2025 to stockholders of record as of November 12, 2025.

headline: United Rentals Announces Strong Third Quarter 2025 Results and Raises Full-Year Guidance for Revenue and Capital Spending Supported by Strong Customer Demand
